## 4. NextAuth Configuration (Backend Responsibilities)

Location:
- `app/api/auth/[...nextauth]/route.ts` (route)
- `src/services/auth/nextAuthOptions.ts` (config)
- `src/services/auth/nextAuthAdapter.ts` (Prisma adapter wiring, reused via services/repositories)

Key design points:
- Providers:
  - Credentials (email/password).
  - Google OAuth.
  - Apple Sign In (with private relay support).
- Adapter:
  - Use Prisma models `User`, `Account`, `Session`.
  - No additional business logic inside adapter; only persistence.
- Callbacks:
  - `signIn`:
    - Enforce:
      - Email/password validity (delegated to `authService.verifyCredentials`).
      - Account state:
        - Deny if `accountState === "locked"` or `User.status` ∈ `{suspended, banned, deleted}`.
        - Allow limited session if `accountState === "email_unverified"`; gating enforced by middleware, not NextAuth alone.
    - Ensure no enumeration in error messages (NFR-PRIV-001).
  - `session`:
    - Embed minimal snapshot of account state (e.g. `accountState`, `ageStatus`, `role`).
    - Do **not** embed sensitive PII or provider metadata.
  - `jwt`:
    - Handle session rotation per Q3: rotate on sign-in and at max every 12h; enforce absolute 30d cap.
  - `redirect`:
    - Ensure safe redirect rules (no open redirects).

Security / Compliance tie-in:
- All secrets (NextAuth secret, provider client IDs/secrets, Veriff keys) are env-only.
- `.env.example` will be updated to include:
  - `NEXTAUTH_SECRET`
  - `NEXTAUTH_URL`
  - `GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID`, `GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET`
  - `APPLE_CLIENT_ID`, `APPLE_TEAM_ID`, `APPLE_KEY_ID`, `APPLE_PRIVATE_KEY` (or equivalent).
  - `VERIFF_API_KEY`, `VERIFF_WEBHOOK_SECRET`
- No secrets in logs; only masked or non-sensitive metadata.

